    <text>
    <body>
        <p>First Lieutenant, 48th Kentucky Volunteer Mounted Infantry Regiment (U.S.A.). Mustered in on August 15, 1863. Wrote a Letter to Thomas E. Bramlette in January 1865 requesting permission to raise a regiment for the protection of Hardin County. </p>

